  "text": "The trait obligation fulfillment pipeline in rustc flows through these key files: (1) **ObligationForest** (`rustc_data_structures/src/obligation_forest/mod.rs`) is the core data structure that tracks pending obligations as a forest of trees, processing them iteratively. (2) **FulfillmentContext** (`traits/fulfill.rs`) wraps ObligationForest for trait obligations, calling `select_where_possible` which drives `process_obligations`. (3) **SelectionContext** (`traits/select/mod.rs`) contains the main `select` method and `match_impl` for checking whether a concrete impl matches a trait obligation. (4) **Candidate assembly** (`traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs`) implements `assemble_candidates` which gathers all possible ways to satisfy a trait bound (impl candidates, builtin candidates, etc.). (5) **Confirmation** (`traits/select/confirmation.rs`) implements `confirm_candidate` which validates and fully checks a selected candidate. (6) **Matching** (`traits/select/_match.rs`) provides `MatchAgainstFreshVars` for approximate type matching during candidate filtering. (7) **Error reporting** spans several files: `fulfillment_errors.rs` contains `report_selection_error` for unsatisfied bounds, `on_unimplemented.rs` handles `#[rustc_on_unimplemented]` custom error messages, `suggestions.rs` provides fix suggestions, `overflow.rs` handles recursion overflow errors, and `mod.rs` ties the error reporting together.",
